3. The compound according to claim 2, wherein said compound has one or more features selected from the group consisting of: 
(a) Rx is hydrogen, alkyl- or dialkylamino, acetamido, or a C1-4 aliphatic group; 
(b) R1 is T-(Ring D), wherein T is a valence bond or a methylene unit; 
(c) Ring D is a 5-7 membered monocyclic or an 8-10 membered bicyclic aryl or heteroaryl ring; and 
(d) R2 is —R or -T—W—R6 and R2′ is hydrogen, or R2 and R2′ are taken together to form an optionally substituted benzo ring.

